granite3.2:2b systeme_francis utilisateur_francis context 6 0.0 5.94 **Event Details: Triton Museum of Art's 2025 Exhibitions and Online Courses**

**Theme:** The theme for the exhibitions is a blend of various artistic techniques, including painting (Peinture), drawing (Dessin), printmaking (Gravure), photography (Photographie), and mixed media (Techniques mixtes). One of the series focuses on Ancient Egyptian art (Egypte ancienne).

**Eligibility:** This event is open to artists based in the United States, specifically those from California.

**Dates:**
- Submission deadline: 2025/03/21 at midnight PST
- Notification of selection results: April 9 ‚Äì April 11, 2025 (by email)
- Deadline for delivery of work: April 12 ‚Äì April 25, 2025
- Exhibition opens: May 17, 2025
- Artists' Reception: May 17, 2025, 2:00 pm ‚Äì 4:00 pm
- Exhibition closes: August 17, 2025
- Pick-up of artwork from the Museum: August 21 ‚Äì September 5, 2025 (during normal Museum open hours)

**Fees:**
- Entry fee: $20.00/one entry, $10.00 for each additional entry (maximum of 10 entries)
- All fees are non-refundable

**Prize:** Selected artists will receive an **Exhibition** at the Triton Museum of Art in Santa Clara, California.

**Artists' Online Courses:**

1. **Triton Online 2025: Explorations in Drawing (Spring)**
- Instructor: Mei-Ying Dell'Aquila
- Schedule: Wednesdays from April 30th through June 4th, 2025, 3:30PM-5:00PM

2. **Triton Online 2025: Expedition in Watercolor (Spring)**
- Instructor: Jeff Bramschreiber
- Schedule: Friday Evenings from April 4 through June 6, 6:00PM-8:00PM

3. **Triton Online 2025: Artistic Escape to Ancient Egypt (Spring)**
- Instructor: Jeff Bramschreiber
- Schedule: Tuesday Evenings from April 1 through June 3, 6:00PM-8:00PM

**Contact:** For general inquiries, please contact competition@tritonmuseum.org.

**About the Triton Museum of Art:**
For over 55 years, the Triton Museum of Art has been a community hub for local artists and art enthusiasts. Located near the Santa Clara Civic Center, it collects and exhibits contemporary and historical works with an emphasis on Greater Bay Area artists. The museum offers a unique space where students can learn about art and the creative process alongside regional and national artists' works.

**URL:**
- Triton Museum of Art:
- ArtDeadline for this competition: [https://artdeadline.com/ops/](https://artdeadline.com/ops/)

The theme of this event is Pop Art, Ancient Egypt, Drawing, Watercolor painting and it's open to artists from California and other regions within the United States. The deadline for submission of entries is March 21st, 2025. The exhibition will be opened on May 17th, 2025 with an artist's reception party held between 2:00 pm and 4:00 pm. The exhibition will close on August 17th, 2025. Pick-up of artwork from the Museum is scheduled to take place during normal Museum open hours which are Tuesdays ‚Äì Sundays, between 11am ‚Äì 4:30pm.

The event includes a workshop series titled Sweet Pop Art: A Playful Painting Camp with Mei-Ying Dell'Aquila held on Wednesdays from April 30th through June 4th, 2025. The other two workshops are Triton Online 2025: Explorations in Drawing (Spring) and Triton Online 2025: Expedition in Watercolor (Spring) both held on Friday evenings with a duration of 6:00 pm-8:00pm from April 4th through June 6, 2025. The last workshop is Triton Online 2025: Artistic Escape to Ancient Egypt (Spring) and it's held on Tuesday evenings starting from April 1st through June 3rd, 2025.

The entry fee for the exhibition is $20.00/one entry, $10.00 for each additional entry. The maximum number of entries is 10 and all fees are non-refundable. Artists will be notified of selection results (acceptance and non-acceptance) by email between Wednesday, April 9 ‚Äì Friday, April 11, 2025.

The Museum is not involved in the selling of artists‚Äô work and will receive no commission. All purchase inquiries will be passed directly to the artist.

For 55 years, the Triton Museum of Art has been a destination for the community, providing a venue where local artists exhibit their work alongside regional and national artists, and where students of all ages learn about art and the creative process. Located across the street from the Santa Clara Civic Center, the Triton Museum of Art collects and exhibits contemporary and historical works with an emphasis on artists of the Greater Bay Area.

Please note: The Museum will be closed on Sunday, April 20, 2025 in observance of the Easter holiday.

The URL for this event is https://artdeadline.com/ops/triton/ and for Triton Museum of Art is https://www.tritonmuseum.org/.

The theme of this event is Pop Art, Ancient Egypt, Drawing, Watercolor painting and it's open to artists from California and other regions within the United States. The deadline for submission of entries is March 21st, 2025. The exhibition will be opened on May 17th, 2025 with an artist's reception party held between 2:00 pm and 4:00 pm. The exhibition will close on August 17th, 2025. Pick-up of artwork from the Museum is scheduled to take place during normal Museum open hours which are Tuesdays ‚Äì Sundays, between 11am ‚Äì 4:30pm.

The event includes a workshop series titled Sweet Pop Art: A Playful Painting Camp with Mei-Ying Dell'Aquila held on Wednesdays from April 30th through June 4th, 2025. The other two workshops are Triton Online 2025: Explorations in Drawing (Spring) and Triton Online 2025: Expedition in Watercolor (Spring) both held on Friday evenings with a duration of 6:00 pm-8:00pm from April 4th through June 6, 2025. The last workshop is Triton Online 2025: Artistic Escape to Ancient Egypt (Spring) and it's held on Tuesday evenings starting from April 1st through June 3rd, 2025.

The entry fee for the exhibition is $20.00/one entry, $10.00 for each additional entry. The maximum number of entries is 10 and all fees are non-refundable. Artists will be notified of selection results (acceptance and non-acceptance) by email between Wednesday, April 9 ‚Äì Friday, April 11, 2025.

The Museum is not involved in the selling of artists‚Äô work and will receive no commission. All purchase inquiries will be passed directly to the artist.

For 55 years, the Triton Museum of Art has been a destination for the community, providing a venue where local artists exhibit their work alongside regional and national artists, and where students of all ages learn about art and the creative process. Located across the street from the Santa Clara Civic Center, the Triton Museum of Art collects and exhibits contemporary and historical works with an emphasis on artists of the Greater Bay Area.

Please note: The Museum will be closed on Sunday, April 20, 2025 in observance of the Easter holiday.
